WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.400 --> 00:00:05.370
- My big pro tip is always break it up.

2
00:00:05.370 --> 00:00:07.950
Break it up in terms
of the different blocks

3
00:00:07.950 --> 00:00:09.630
of the app that you're trying to make.

4
00:00:09.630 --> 00:00:12.367
So, one, it's always helpful
to actually tell the model,

5
00:00:12.367 --> 00:00:14.250
"Here's the project
we're making as a whole,"

6
00:00:14.250 --> 00:00:16.890
so it understands the whole
picture or the whole story

7
00:00:16.890 --> 00:00:18.630
of the thing you're about to make.

8
00:00:18.630 --> 00:00:19.987
Then, you can actually say,

9
00:00:19.987 --> 00:00:21.900
"Cool, I have this app I'm going to make.

10
00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:23.820
Let's start with the first part."

11
00:00:23.820 --> 00:00:25.687
And then, when it does
that first part, say,

12
00:00:25.687 --> 00:00:27.060
"Now, let's do the second part."

13
00:00:27.060 --> 00:00:29.010
And you can build it brick by brick.

14
00:00:29.010 --> 00:00:31.080
And when you do that, it's helpful,

15
00:00:31.080 --> 00:00:33.300
because one, it'll probably get it right

16
00:00:33.300 --> 00:00:35.040
because it's actually focusing

17
00:00:35.040 --> 00:00:37.560
on the very specific
tasks you're giving it.

18
00:00:37.560 --> 00:00:40.530
But two, it's actually
easier to correct errors

19
00:00:40.530 --> 00:00:43.470
because if you ask it to
make this whole big thing,

20
00:00:43.470 --> 00:00:46.140
you don't actually know
where it messed up.

21
00:00:46.140 --> 00:00:47.520
But if you're doing brick by brick,

22
00:00:47.520 --> 00:00:51.060
you know exactly which one
actually causes that fault.

23
00:00:51.060 --> 00:00:53.160
So, be a little patient with it

24
00:00:53.160 --> 00:00:54.690
and break it up into steps

25
00:00:54.690 --> 00:00:56.910
just like you would if you
were to give any person

26
00:00:56.910 --> 00:00:58.440
a really complex task,

27
00:00:58.440 --> 00:01:00.003
and it'll go a long way.